 After, every scrub bar drag and +30s/-30s tap fires an immediate `PUT` with a JSON body. More requests = more chances to trigger for a borderline-threat IP.\n\n2. **WebSocket upgrade requests** (v7.1.3+) — The `Upgrade: websocket` + `Connection: upgrade` headers with the handshake payload can look unusual to WAF pattern matching.\n\n3. **Search queries in URLs** — `?search=O'Brien` or any title with apostrophes/special chars in the search box goes through `encodeURIComponent` but Cloudflare's SQLi rules inspect the decoded value.\n\nMy bet is #3 — she searches for a book, the title has an apostrophe, Cloudflare sees `search=something'...` from a high-threat IP, and blocks it as SQLi. That search endpoint existed before but the Back Office search in utilities.js was added in the 7.1.x series.\n\nThe WAF exception for authenticated sessions is still the right fix either way. Want me to set it up?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":496,"cache_read_input_tokens":122263,"output_tokens":916,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":496,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZN7gnjkZso2QUurnp9Cx","type":"assistant","uuid":"27f788de-5aa8-4c93-b591-148d363d3eb7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:09:18.812Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/hddRaid1/ClaudeCodeProjects/Audiobook-Manager","sessionId":"d4f7c8f8-1fae-457f-9294-519347b1520a","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"serene-booping-church"}
