{"parentUuid":"0580430d-fe79-4f77-b15f-2351c742014a","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"df536320-6f46-4166-94b0-241928cda50a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"<command-message>close</command-message>\n<command-name>/close</command-name>"},"uuid":"8ed9f219-b8f4-4762-97d8-8be3d84d08c0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:12:40.463Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/hddRaid1/ClaudeCodeProjects/Audiobook-Manager","sessionId":"d4f7c8f8-1fae-457f-9294-519347b1520a","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"serene-booping-church"}
{"parentUuid":"8ed9f219-b8f4-4762-97d8-8be3d84d08c0","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"df536320-6f46-4166-94b0-241928cda50a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Close Project\n\nClose the current Claude Code project session with proper cleanup.\n\n## What This Does\n\n1. Creates exit timestamp file in project directory\n2. Increments session count\n3. Commits all uncommitted changes (auto-generated message)\n4. Pushes to remote if project has a GitHub repo\n5. Saves checkpoint (if checkpoint script or notes exist)\n6. Finalizes the session record with closing summary\n7. Runs exit diagnostics (git status, unpushed commits, dev servers, Docker, TODOs, sudo)\n8. Clears current project state\n9. Disables all MCP plugins (reset to baseline)\n\n## Current Project\n\n```bash\nSTATE_FILE=\"$HOME/.claude/.current_project\"\nif [ -f \"$STATE_FILE\" ]; then\n    PROJECT_DIR=$(cat \"$STATE_FILE\")\n    echo \"Current project: $PROJECT_DIR\"\nelse\n    echo \"No project currently open (state file missing)\"\n    echo \"Using PWD as fallback\"\nfi\n```\n\n## Execute Close\n\nRun the close sequence. This must be done step by step:\n\n### Step 1: Get Project Directory\n\n```bash\nSTATE_FILE=\"$HOME/.claude/.current_project\"\nif [ -f \"$STATE_FILE\" ]; then\n    PROJECT_DIR=$(cat \"$STATE_FILE\")\nelse\n    PROJECT_DIR=\"$PWD\"\nfi\n\n# Validate it's a Claude project\nif [[ \"$PROJECT_DIR\" != /hddRaid1/ClaudeCodeProjects/* ]]; then\n    echo \"⚠ Not in a project directory: $PROJECT_DIR\"\n    echo \"No exit file created.\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\necho \"Closing project: $(basename \"$PROJECT_DIR\")\"\necho \"PROJECT_DIR=$PROJECT_DIR\"\n```\n\n### Step 2: Create Exit Timestamp\n\n```bash\nPROJECT_DIR=$(cat ~/.claude/.current_project 2>/dev/null || echo \"$PWD\")\nproject_name=$(basename \"$PROJECT_DIR\")\nts=$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)\n\n# Remove old exit files and create new one\nrm -f \"$PROJECT_DIR\"/exit.* 2>/dev/null\ntouch \"$PROJECT_DIR/exit.$ts\"\necho \"✓ Exit timestamp: $ts\"\n```\n\n### Step 3: Increment Session Count\n\n```bash\nPROJECT_DIR=$(cat ~/.claude/.current_project 2>/dev/null || echo \"$PWD\")\nCOUNT_FILE=\"$PROJECT_DIR/.session-count\"\nif [ -f \"$COUNT_FILE\" ]; then\n    count=$(cat \"$COUNT_FILE\")\n    count=$((count + 1))\nelse\n    count=1\nfi\necho \"$count\" > \"$COUNT_FILE\"\necho \"✓ Session count: $count\"\n```\n\n### Step 4: Commit and Push\n\n```bash\nPROJECT_DIR=$(cat ~/.claude/.current_project 2>/dev/null || echo \"$PWD\")\ncd \"$PROJECT_DIR\" || true\n\n# Check for uncommitted changes (staged + unstaged + untracked)\nchanges=$(git status --porcelain 2>/dev/null)\nif [ -n \"$changes\" ]; then\n    # Stage all changes\n    git add -A\n\n    # Commit with auto-generated message\n    file_count=$(echo \"$changes\" | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n    git commit -m \"chore: session close — $file_count file(s) auto-committed\" 2>/dev/null\n    echo \"✓ Committed $file_count file(s)\"\nelse\n    echo \"○ No uncommitted changes\"\nfi\n\n# Push if remote exists\nremote=$(git remote 2>/dev/null | head -1)\nif [ -n \"$remote\" ]; then\n    branch=$(git branch --show-current 2>/dev/null)\n    if git push \"$remote\" \"$branch\" 2>/dev/null; then\n        echo \"✓ Pushed to $remote/$branch\"\n    else\n        echo \"⚠ Push failed — may need manual resolution\"\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"○ No remote — local-only project\"\nfi\n```\n\n### Step 5: Save Checkpoint\n\n```bash\nPROJECT_DIR=$(cat ~/.claude/.current_project 2>/dev/null || echo \"$PWD\")\nCHECKPOINT_SCRIPT=\"$PROJECT_DIR/.claude-checkpoint-update.sh\"\nproject_name=$(basename \"$PROJECT_DIR\")\n\n# Run custom checkpoint script if it exists\nif [ -x \"$CHECKPOINT_SCRIPT\" ]; then\n    echo \"Running checkpoint script...\"\n    if bash \"$CHECKPOINT_SCRIPT\" --once 2>/dev/null; then\n        echo \"✓ Checkpoint: saved (via script)\"\n    else\n        echo \"⚠ Checkpoint script failed, creating basic checkpoint...\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Always create/update basic checkpoint with git state\ncd \"$PROJECT_DIR\" || true\nbranch=$(git branch --show-current 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\ncommit=$(git log -1 --format=\"%h - %s\" 2>/dev/null | head -c 70 || echo \"unknown\")\nuncommitted=$(git status --porcelain 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\nstaged=$(git diff --cached --name-only 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\nnotes=\"\"\nif [ -f \"$PROJECT_DIR/.claude-checkpoint-notes.md\" ]; then\n    notes=$(cat \"$PROJECT_DIR/.claude-checkpoint-notes.md\")\nfi\n\ncat > \"$PROJECT_DIR/.claude-checkpoint\" << EOF\nCheckpoint: $(date \"+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z\")\nProject: $project_name\nBranch: $branch\nCommit: $commit\nUncommitted files: $uncommitted\nStaged files: $staged\n\n--- Notes ---\n$notes\nEOF\n\necho \"✓ Checkpoint: saved\"\necho \"  Branch: $branch | Uncommitted: $uncommitted files\"\n```\n\n### Step 6: Finalize Session Record\n\nAppend a closing entry to the session record. This captures the final state of work\nso the next session (or a resume) can pick up where this one left off.\n\n```bash\nPROJECT_DIR=$(cat ~/.claude/.current_project 2>/dev/null || echo \"$PWD\")\n\n# Update wallet card with closed state\nwallet_card=\"$PROJECT_DIR/.claude-task-state.md\"\nif [[ -f \"$wallet_card\" ]]; then\n    cat > \"$wallet_card\" << WALLETEOF\n---\nupdated: $(date -Iseconds)\nsession: closed\nbranch: $(git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" branch --show-current 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n---\n# Task State\n\n## Current Work\nSession closed normally.\n\n## Next Step\nNo pending work.\nWALLETEOF\n    echo \"✓ Wallet card: marked as closed\"\nfi\n\n# Mark session context file as closed (so next session detects clean exit)\ncontext_file=\"$PROJECT_DIR/.claude-session-context.md\"\nif [[ -f \"$context_file\" ]]; then\n    # Update frontmatter session field to \"closed\"\n    sed -i 's/^session: .*/session: closed/' \"$context_file\"\n    echo \"✓ Session context: marked as closed\"\nfi\n\n# Delete ring buffer (no longer needed after clean close)\nring_file=\"$PROJECT_DIR/.claude-session-ring.jsonl\"\nif [[ -f \"$ring_file\" ]]; then\n    rm -f \"$ring_file\"\n    echo \"✓ Ring buffer: deleted\"\nfi\n\ntoday=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d')\ntimestamp=$(date '+%H:%M:%S')\nsession_file=\"$PROJECT_DIR/SESSION_RECORD_${today}.md\"\n\n# Also check the no-project record location\nif [[ ! -f \"$session_file\" ]]; then\n    session_file=\"$HOME/.claude/session-records/SESSION_RECORD_${today}.md\"\nfi\n\nif [[ -f \"$session_file\" ]]; then\n    # Gather final git state\n    cd \"$PROJECT_DIR\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    branch=$(git branch --show-current 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n    last_commit=$(git log -1 --format=\"%h - %s\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"none\")\n    uncommitted=$(git status --porcelain 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n\n    # Write closing entry\n    {\n        echo \"\"\n        echo \"### [$timestamp] SESSION CLOSED\"\n        echo \"- Branch: \\`$branch\\`\"\n        echo \"- Last commit: $last_commit\"\n        echo \"- Uncommitted files at close: $uncommitted\"\n        echo \"- Session closed via /close\"\n        echo \"\"\n    } >> \"$session_file\"\n\n    echo \"✓ Session record finalized: $session_file\"\nelse\n    echo \"○ No session record found to finalize\"\nfi\n```\n\n**IMPORTANT**: Before running the above script, you (Claude) MUST append your own summary\nto the session record. Use the Edit or Bash tool to add a section BEFORE the closing\nentry with:\n- What was worked on this session (tasks completed, features added, bugs fixed)\n- Key decisions made\n- Any pending/unfinished work the next session should pick up\n- Files that were created or significantly modified\n\nThis is the most valuable part of the session record — the automated git state above\nis just metadata. Your summary of the *intent* and *context* is what makes the next\nsession productive.\n\n### Step 7: Exit Diagnostics\n\nRun the exit checklist to report anything that needs attention before the session ends.\n\n```bash\nPROJECT_DIR=$(cat ~/.claude/.current_project 2>/dev/null || echo \"$PWD\")\n\noutput=\"\"\n\n# Git status\nif [[ -d \"$PROJECT_DIR/.git\" ]]; then\n    git_status=$(git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" status --short 2>/dev/null)\n    if [[ -n \"$git_status\" ]]; then\n        uncommitted=$(echo \"$git_status\" | wc -l)\n        output+=\"Git: $uncommitted uncommitted file(s)\\n\"\n    else\n        output+=\"Git: Working tree clean\\n\"\n    fi\n\n    # Unpushed commits\n    upstream=$(git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" rev-parse --abbrev-ref '@{upstream}' 2>/dev/null)\n    if [[ -n \"$upstream\" ]]; then\n        unpushed=$(git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" log '@{upstream}..HEAD' --oneline 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n        if (( unpushed > 0 )); then\n            output+=\"Unpushed: $unpushed commit(s) not pushed\\n\"\n        else\n            output+=\"Pushed: All commits pushed\\n\"\n        fi\n    else\n        has_commits=$(git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" rev-parse HEAD 2>/dev/null)\n        has_remote=$(git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" remote 2>/dev/null | head -1)\n        if [[ -n \"$has_commits\" ]] && [[ -n \"$has_remote\" ]]; then\n            output+=\"Unpushed: Branch not tracking remote\\n\"\n        else\n            output+=\"Unpushed: No remote configured\\n\"\n        fi\n    fi\n\n    # Clean up local branches whose upstream is gone (merged & deleted on GitHub)\n    gone_branches=$(git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" branch -vv 2>/dev/null | grep ': gone]' | awk '{print }')\n    if [[ -n \"$gone_branches\" ]]; then\n        gone_count=$(echo \"$gone_branches\" | wc -l)\n        echo \"$gone_branches\" | xargs -r git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" branch -d 2>/dev/null\n        output+=\"Branch cleanup: deleted $gone_count merged local branch(es) whose remote was deleted\\n\"\n    fi\n\n    # Git stashes\n    stash_count=$(git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" stash list 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    if (( stash_count > 0 )); then\n        output+=\"Stashes: $stash_count stash(es) saved\\n\"\n    fi\n\n    # TODOs in uncommitted changes\n    todo_count=$(git -C \"$PROJECT_DIR\" diff HEAD 2>/dev/null | grep -cE '^\\+.*(TODO|FIXME|XXX|HACK)') || todo_count=0\n    if (( todo_count > 0 )); then\n        output+=\"TODOs: $todo_count new TODO/FIXME in uncommitted changes\\n\"\n    fi\nelse\n    output+=\"Git: Not a repository\\n\"\nfi\n\n# Running dev servers (common ports)\ndev_ports=(3000 3001 5173 8000 8888 4200 9000)\nrunning_servers=\"\"\nfor port in \"${dev_ports[@]}\"; do\n    if ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | grep -q \":$port \"; then\n        running_servers+=\"$port \"\n    fi\ndone\nif [[ -n \"$running_servers\" ]]; then\n    output+=\"Dev servers: ports ${running_servers}still listening\\n\"\nfi\n\n# Docker containers\nif command -v docker &>/dev/null; then\n    running_containers=$(docker ps -q 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    if (( running_containers > 0 )); then\n        container_names=$(docker ps --format '{{.Names}}' 2>/dev/null | head -3 | tr '\\n' ' ')\n        output+=\"Docker: $running_containers container(s) running ($container_names)\\n\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Lingering sudo/root processes\nroot_procs=$(pgrep -u root -P 1 --ns $$ 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\nif (( root_procs > 0 )); then\n    output+=\"Sudo processes: $root_procs root process(es) may cause EPERM on /exit\\n\"\nfi\n\nif [[ -n \"$output\" ]]; then\n    echo \"--- Exit Diagnostics ---\"\n    echo -e \"$output\"\n    echo \"------------------------\"\nelse\n    echo \"--- Exit Diagnostics: All clear ---\"\nfi\n```\n\n### Step 8: Clear State and Reset MCP\n\n```bash\nPROJECT_DIR=$(cat ~/.claude/.current_project 2>/dev/null || echo \"$PWD\")\nproject_name=$(basename \"$PROJECT_DIR\")\n\n# Clear current project state\nrm -f ~/.claude/.current_project\necho \"✓ Cleared current-project state\"\n\n# Clean up stale compaction flags\nrm -f ~/.claude/cache/compaction-pending-* 2>/dev/null\necho \"✓ Compaction flags: cleaned\"\n\n# Disable all MCP plugins\nif [ -x ~/.claude/scripts/mcp-toggle.sh ]; then\n    mcp_result=$(~/.claude/scripts/mcp-toggle.sh --disable-all 2>&1)\n    echo \"✓ MCP plugins: disabled\"\nelse\n    echo \"○ MCP toggle script not found\"\nfi\n\n# Log to hooks log\necho \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] [Close] Closed project: $project_name\" >> ~/.claude/logs/hooks.log\n\necho \"\"\necho \"═══════════════════════════════════════\"\necho \"✓ Closed project: $project_name\"\necho \"  Type /exit to end the session.\"\necho \"═══════════════════════════════════════\"\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- The exit timestamp file (e.g., `exit.20260125-213000`) marks when the project was last closed\n- Session count tracks how many times the project has been opened/closed\n- All uncommitted changes are auto-committed before closing\n- Projects with a GitHub remote are automatically pushed after commit (commits only — NEVER creates tags, version bumps, or releases; those require explicit `/git-release`)\n- Local-only projects (no remote) are committed but not pushed\n- Checkpoints allow resuming work with \"continue from checkpoint\"\n- Session record is finalized with both an automated closing entry AND Claude's own summary of work done\n- Exit diagnostics report dangling state (unpushed commits, dev servers, Docker, TODOs, sudo processes)\n- MCP plugins are disabled to reset to baseline for next session\n- The \"bye\" command functionality is fully incorporated — typing \"bye\" is no longer needed\n"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"b68ad230-79d8-43dd-a67a-5e04cd0a2d35","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:12:40.463Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/hddRaid1/ClaudeCodeProjects/Audiobook-Manager","sessionId":"d4f7c8f8-1fae-457f-9294-519347b1520a","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"serene-booping-church"}
